# Theme Build Guide — Minimal Grid

**Goal:** Apply a clean, modern, lightweight theme that highlights photos with minimal UI.  
**Branch:** `theme/minimal-grid`  
**Scope:** Typography, color tokens, buttons, grid/galleries, subtle hover/zoom. No content changes.

---

## Design Direction

- **Vibe:** Crisp, calm, gallery-first.
- **Fonts:** Inter for UI, optional Playfair Display for big headings.
- **Colors:** White background, near-black text, cool accent.
- **Layout:** Even grid, generous whitespace, centered containers (already in main).
- **Motion:** Tiny scale/opacity on hover; no heavy animations.

---

## Files to Modify

- `/css/style.css` → **override tokens + small utilities only** (keep it minimal).
- HTML **only if needed** for class hooks (e.g., add `.tile` class on gallery links). Do not change content.

> Note: `baseline-style.css` handles structure (containers, hero, cards, gallery columns). This theme only adjusts tokens and small add-ons.

---

## Tokens & Rules (Copilot: implement these)

### 1) CSS Variables (in `/css/style.css`)
Override just the variables and a few small utilities:

```css
/* ===== theme/minimal-grid overrides ===== */
:root {
  /* Palette */
  --bg: #ffffff;
  --text: #111827;             /* slate-900 */
  --muted-text: #6b7280;       /* slate-500 */
  --accent: #2563eb;           /* blue-600 */
  --accent-600: #1d4ed8;       /* blue-700 */
  --border: #e5e7eb;           /* gray-200 */
  --card: #ffffff;

  /* Type & radii */
  --font-sans: "Inter", system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;
  --radius: 14px;
  --radius-sm: 10px;

  /* Spacing */
  --gutter: 1.25rem;
  --space-lg: 1.5rem;
  --space-xl: 2.25rem;
}

/* Headings tighten up, body comfortable */
h1, h2, h3 { letter-spacing: .2px; }
p { margin: 0 0 0.85rem; }

/* Buttons: minimal, rounded, strong accent */
.button, button, input[type="submit"] {
  background: var(--accent);
  border-color: var(--accent);
  border-radius: 999px;
}
.button:hover, button:hover, input[type="submit"]:hover {
  background: var(--accent-600);
}

/* Nav links: understated until hover */
nav.site-nav a {
  opacity: .9;
  transition: opacity .15s ease, background .2s ease;
}
nav.site-nav a:hover { opacity: 1; }

/* Hero alignment: left on desktop, centered on small */
.hero p.lead { color: var(--muted-text); }

/* Grid tiles: tidy shadows + hover zoom */
.tile {
  transition: transform .18s ease, box-shadow .25s ease, border-color .2s ease;
}
.tile:hover {
  transform: translateY(-1px) scale(1.01);
  box-shadow: 0 10px 28px rgba(0,0,0,.08);
  border-color: rgba(37,99,235,.25);
}

/* Gallery thumbnails: subtle fade-in */
.gallery a img {
  transition: transform .18s ease, opacity .25s ease;
  opacity: .98;
}
.gallery a:hover img {
  transform: scale(1.01);
  opacity: 1;
}

/* Cards: keep airy and consistent */
.card { border-radius: var(--radius); }

/* Footer: low-contrast, roomy */
footer.site-footer { color: var(--muted-text); }
```

### 2) Optional Google Fonts (HTML `<head>`)
If not already present, add:
```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600&family=Playfair+Display:wght@600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
```

> If Playfair is used, only for H1/H2 on index/hero:
```css
h1, .display-serif { font-family: "Playfair Display", Georgia, serif; }
```

### 3) Class hooks (HTML) — only if missing
Ensure gallery items use the `.tile` wrapper so hover/zoom applies:
```html
<a href="/images/weddings/large-01.jpg" class="tile" data-pswp-width="1600" data-pswp-height="1067">
  <img src="/images/weddings/thumb-01.jpg" alt="Bride and groom at sunset">
  <span class="overlay"></span>
  <span class="label">View</span>
</a>
```

---

## Accessibility & Performance

- All images must have meaningful `alt` text (already scaffolded).
- Use `loading="lazy"` on gallery thumbs.
- Keep motion subtle; respect reduced motion if you add bigger effects later.

---

## Acceptance Criteria (Copilot: verify before committing)

- [ ] Typography uses Inter; headings look crisp; spacing comfortable.
- [ ] Accent color updated across buttons/links.
- [ ] Hero + sections remain centered within `.container`.
- [ ] Gallery tiles show **subtle hover zoom** and feel clickable.
- [ ] No layout regressions on mobile (≤ 400px) or large screens (≥ 1440px).
- [ ] Lighthouse Performance ≥ 90 and Accessibility ≥ 90 on the homepage (local run ok).

---

## Git & Preview

```bash
# create and push branch
git checkout -b theme/minimal-grid
git add -A
git commit -m "theme(minimal-grid): tokens, buttons, grid hover, typography"
git push -u origin theme/minimal-grid
```

Set up your per-branch preview (Netlify/Vercel/GitHub Pages).  
Add a **screenshot** and the **preview URL** to this README when deployed.

